   Facts & Figures: China's Exports to Finland in 1st 4 Months 

   Following are the latest facts and figures on China's major export
   commodities to Finland in the first four months of 2000, provided by
   the General Administration of Customs:

   -- Machines, electronic goods, audiovisual equipment and relevant parts
   and accessories: 133.621 million U.S. dollars.

   -- Textile material and products: 17.053 million U.S. dollars.

   -- Base metals and related products: 7.882 million U.S. dollars.

   -- Plastics, rubber and related products: 6.796 million U.S. dollars.

   -- Optical and medical equipment, clocks, watches and musical
   instruments: 6.154 million U.S. dollars.
